{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.13","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[],"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":5,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/amirankapanadze/lay4castpublic?scriptVersionId=334880057\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown"},{"id":"85c73f24-adf0-48e4-8050-bad93b391f7c","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Lay4Cast — Honest Methodology Notebook\n\n**What this notebook is:** a transparent record of testing whether a stock\nprediction model (Prophet + Random Forest + real market/sentiment data)\nactually beats chance — including every failed attempt, every fixed bug,\nand the final, honest result.\n\n**What this notebook is not:** a pitch. If you're looking for a model that\nclaims 90% accuracy, this isn't it. Every number below is walk-forward\nvalidated against a naive baseline, and reported as-is, win or lose.\n\n**Why publish the failures too:** most public \"AI stock predictor\" notebooks\nonly show the version that worked. This one shows the full path — including\na real data-leakage bug that was caught and fixed, and a final sentiment\ntest that was pre-registered against a 55% threshold *before* running it,\nspecifically so the result couldn't be quietly reframed as a win after the fact.\n\n---\n","metadata":{}},{"id":"d69b4944-9635-464d-8522-cb547c451010","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 1. Setup","metadata":{}},{"id":"9962a996-44c1-4dff-909a-649b948ee0a9","cell_type":"code","source":"import pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nimport yfinance as yf\nfrom prophet import Prophet\nfrom sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor, HistGradientBoostingClassifier\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\nfrom sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error, accuracy_score\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T19:23:36.837161Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T19:23:36.83741Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-13T19:23:44.499236Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-13T19:23:36.837386Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-13T19:23:44.497326Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":1},{"id":"81e20358-dd7d-4eb0-b9b5-b9b5dbbcb234","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 2. Single-Stock Baseline (AAPL)\n\n**The question:** can Prophet + Random Forest predict tomorrow's AAPL close\nbetter than just guessing \"tomorrow = today\"?\n\n**The leakage bug we caught:** the first version of this test fit Prophet on\nthe *entire* dataset before splitting train/test — meaning the model had\ntechnically already \"seen\" the test period's price trend during training.\nThat produced an artificially good-looking MAE. The version below fixes\nthis: Prophet is fit **only** on the training window, then forecasts forward\ninto the test period the same way it would in live, real-time use.","metadata":{}},{"id":"562f9b31-8fee-40b8-9c24-21dfe587b7a0","cell_type":"code","source":"TICKER = \"AAPL\"\ndf = yf.download(TICKER, period=\"3y\").reset_index()\nif isinstance(df.columns, pd.MultiIndex):\n    df.columns = df.columns.get_level_values(0)\ndf[\"Date\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\"Date\"]).dt.tz_localize(None)\ndf = df[[\"Date\", \"Close\", \"Volume\"]].dropna()\n\nsplit_idx = int(len(df) * 0.8)\ntrain_df = df.iloc[:split_idx].copy()\ntest_df = df.iloc[split_idx:].copy()\nprint(f\"Train: {train_df['Date'].min().date()} to {train_df['Date'].max().date()}\")\nprint(f\"Test:  {test_df['Date'].min().date()} to {test_df['Date'].max().date()}\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T19:23:44.502154Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T19:23:44.502818Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-13T19:23:45.382364Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-13T19:23:44.502773Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-13T19:23:45.37913Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"/tmp/ipykernel_58/556963481.py:2: FutureWarning: YF.download() has changed argument auto_adjust default to True\n  df = yf.download(TICKER, period=\"3y\").reset_index()\n[*********************100%***********************]  1 of 1 completed","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"Train: 2023-07-13 to 2025-12-02\nTest:  2025-12-03 to 2026-07-13\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":2},{"id":"e74c324d-5a3a-4e6c-bc9b-e7a5d9165ee6","cell_type":"code","source":"# Fit Prophet ONLY on training data — no lookahead\nprophet_train = train_df.rename(columns={\"Date\": \"ds\", \"Close\": \"y\"})[[\"ds\", \"y\"]]\nm = Prophet(daily_seasonality=False, weekly_seasonality=True, yearly_seasonality=True)\nm.fit(prophet_train)\n\nfuture = m.make_future_dataframe(periods=int(len(test_df) * 1.6))\nforecast = m.predict(future)\n\ndef add_features(data):\n    data = data.copy()\n    data[\"MA5\"] = data[\"Close\"].rolling(5).mean()\n    data[\"MA10\"] = data[\"Close\"].rolling(10).mean()\n    data[\"Vol_MA5\"] = data[\"Volume\"].rolling(5).mean()\n    data[\"Target_Next_Close\"] = data[\"Close\"].shift(-1)\n    return data\n\ntrain_feat = add_features(train_df).dropna()\ntest_feat = add_features(test_df).dropna()\n\nfc = forecast[[\"ds\", \"yhat\"]].rename(columns={\"ds\": \"Date\", \"yhat\": \"Prophet_yhat\"})\ntrain_feat = train_feat.merge(fc, on=\"Date\", how=\"left\")\ntest_feat = test_feat.merge(fc, on=\"Date\", how=\"left\")\n\nprint(\"NaNs after merge (should be 0):\", train_feat[\"Prophet_yhat\"].isna().sum(), test_feat[\"Prophet_yhat\"].isna().sum())\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T19:23:45.393161Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T19:23:45.39487Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-13T19:23:48.920326Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-13T19:23:45.394817Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-13T19:23:48.919246Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"19:23:47 - cmdstanpy - INFO - Chain [1] start processing\n19:23:47 - cmdstanpy - INFO - Chain [1] done processing\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"NaNs after merge (should be 0): 0 0\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":3},{"id":"8077e5c0-95a9-4f4b-ab92-3d3e357b5b8d","cell_type":"code","source":"FEATURES = [\"MA5\", \"MA10\", \"Vol_MA5\", \"Prophet_yhat\"]\nX_train, y_train = train_feat[FEATURES], train_feat[\"Target_Next_Close\"]\nX_test, y_test = test_feat[FEATURES], test_feat[\"Target_Next_Close\"]\n\nrf = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=300, random_state=42)\nrf.fit(X_train, y_train)\npreds = rf.predict(X_test)\n\nmodel_mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, preds)\nnaive_preds = test_feat[\"Close\"].values\nnaive_mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, naive_preds)\n\nprint(f\"Model MAE:  {model_mae:.3f}\")\nprint(f\"Naive MAE:  {naive_mae:.3f}  (predicting tomorrow = today's close)\")\nprint(f\"Model {'beats' if model_mae < naive_mae else 'does NOT beat'} the naive baseline\")\n\nactual_dir = np.sign(y_test.values - test_feat[\"Close\"].values)\nmodel_dir = np.sign(preds - test_feat[\"Close\"].values)\ndir_acc = np.mean(actual_dir == model_dir)\nprint(f\"\\nDirectional accuracy: {dir_acc:.1%} (50% = coin flip)\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T19:23:48.921625Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T19:23:48.922066Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-13T19:23:50.28727Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-13T19:23:48.922027Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-13T19:23:50.285929Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Model MAE:  14.775\nNaive MAE:  3.201  (predicting tomorrow = today's close)\nModel does NOT beat the naive baseline\n\nDirectional accuracy: 51.1% (50% = coin flip)\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":4},{"id":"65fab8b4-f47d-4208-ac38-ee4efa69f38b","cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Result on AAPL alone:** directional accuracy came in barely above a coin\nflip. That's not a failure of engineering — it's the honest starting point.\nA single stock is a small, noisy sample. The next section scales this up\nproperly.","metadata":{}},{"id":"532de163-2ccd-4976-b093-78cac2d54ce8","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 3. Scaling Up — Pooled, Walk-Forward Validated\n\nSingle-stock backtests are easy to fool yourself with. This section:\n- Pools ~98 large-cap tickers together (so the model has to find patterns\n  that generalize across companies, not memorize one stock's history)\n- Predicts **excess return vs. SPY** (strips out \"the whole market went up\"\n  as a cheat signal)\n- Validates across 5 separate, non-overlapping time windows (walk-forward),\n  not a single lucky/unlucky split\n- Compares against an \"always predict up\" baseline — a harder bar than a\n  coin flip, since markets drift upward more often than down","metadata":{}},{"id":"03265869-d87a-4a86-b3c5-6645a345f086","cell_type":"code","source":"TICKERS = [\n    'AAPL','MSFT','NVDA','GOOGL','AMZN','META','TSLA','BRK-B','LLY','AVGO',\n    'JPM','V','UNH','MA','PG','JNJ','HD','COST','CVX','CRM',\n    'AMD','NFLX','ABBV','PEP','BAC','WMT','KO','TMO','LIN','DIS',\n    'MCD','WFC','CSCO','INTC','INTU','QCOM','CAT','TXN','IBM','NOW',\n    'GE','AMGN','AXP','BA','HON','PLTR','SOFI','ROKU',\n    'UBER','COIN','HOOD','DKNG','MARA','RIVN','LCID','NIO','MSTR','RIOT',\n    'PYPL','SHOP','AFRM','SNOW','PINS','CRWD','DDOG','ZS','NET',\n    'PANW','DOCN','MDB','GME','AMC','BABA','JD','PDD','BIDU',\n    'NVO','VRTX','REGN','GILD','ISRG','VRSK','LRCX','MRNA','SNY','NVS',\n    'TMUS','ADI','KLAC','AMAT','MU','NXPI','ARM','SMCI','DELL'\n]\nBENCHMARK = 'SPY'\nraw = yf.download(TICKERS + [BENCHMARK], period=\"3y\", group_by=\"ticker\", progress=False)\n\ndef get_close_volume(ticker):\n    try:\n        d = raw[ticker][['Close','Volume']].reset_index()\n        d.columns = ['Date','Close','Volume']\n        d['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(d['Date']).dt.tz_localize(None)\n        d = d.dropna()\n        return d if len(d) >= 60 else None\n    except Exception:\n        return None\n\nspy = get_close_volume(BENCHMARK)\nspy['Market_Return'] = spy['Close'].pct_change()\nspy = spy[['Date','Market_Return']]\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T19:23:50.289062Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T19:23:50.28953Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-13T19:23:56.77136Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-13T19:23:50.289479Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-13T19:23:56.77032Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"/tmp/ipykernel_58/3885257103.py:14: FutureWarning: YF.download() has changed argument auto_adjust default to True\n  raw = yf.download(TICKERS + [BENCHMARK], period=\"3y\", group_by=\"ticker\", progress=False)\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":5},{"id":"0928a8f5-fc6c-41e9-bcce-dbe43c55eded","cell_type":"code","source":"def build_features(ticker):\n    d = get_close_volume(ticker)\n    if d is None:\n        return None\n    d = d.merge(spy, on='Date', how='inner')\n    d['Return'] = d['Close'].pct_change()\n    d['Excess_Return'] = d['Return'] - d['Market_Return']\n    d['ROC_5'] = d['Close'].pct_change(5)\n    d['ROC_10'] = d['Close'].pct_change(10)\n    d['Volatility_10'] = d['Return'].rolling(10).std()\n    d['Rel_Volume'] = d['Volume'] / d['Volume'].rolling(20).mean()\n    d['MA20'] = d['Close'].rolling(20).mean()\n    d['Price_vs_MA20'] = (d['Close'] - d['MA20']) / d['MA20']\n    d['Target'] = (d['Excess_Return'].shift(-1) > 0).astype(int)\n    d['Ticker'] = ticker\n    return d.dropna()\n\nFEATURES_POOLED = ['ROC_5','ROC_10','Volatility_10','Rel_Volume','Price_vs_MA20','Excess_Return']\nframes = [f for t in TICKERS if (f := build_features(t)) is not None]\nall_data = pd.concat(frames).sort_values('Date').reset_index(drop=True)\nprint(f\"Pooled dataset: {len(all_data)} rows across {len(frames)} tickers\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T19:23:56.77439Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T19:23:56.774686Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-13T19:23:58.079171Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-13T19:23:56.774659Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-13T19:23:58.078099Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Pooled dataset: 69591 rows across 95 tickers\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":6},{"id":"595e05dc-23a0-4cd2-9182-9f7e8904d4a1","cell_type":"code","source":"dates = sorted(all_data['Date'].unique())\nn_folds = 5\nfold_size = len(dates) // (n_folds + 1)\nresults = []\n\nfor fold in range(n_folds):\n    train_end = dates[fold_size * (fold + 1)]\n    test_end = dates[min(fold_size * (fold + 2) - 1, len(dates) - 1)]\n    train = all_data[all_data['Date'] <= train_end]\n    test = all_data[(all_data['Date'] > train_end) & (all_data['Date'] <= test_end)]\n    if len(test) == 0 or len(train) == 0:\n        continue\n\n    X_train, y_train = train[FEATURES_POOLED], train['Target']\n    X_test, y_test = test[FEATURES_POOLED], test['Target']\n\n    clf = HistGradientBoostingClassifier(max_iter=200, max_depth=4, random_state=42)\n    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)\n    preds = clf.predict(X_test)\n\n    acc = accuracy_score(y_test, preds)\n    always_up = accuracy_score(y_test, np.ones(len(y_test)))\n    results.append({\"fold\": fold+1, \"test_start\": test['Date'].min().date(),\n                     \"test_end\": test['Date'].max().date(),\n                     \"model_accuracy\": acc, \"always_up_baseline\": always_up,\n                     \"n_test_rows\": len(test)})\n\nresults_df = pd.DataFrame(results)\nprint(results_df)\nprint(f\"\\nMean model accuracy: {results_df['model_accuracy'].mean():.1%}\")\nprint(f\"Mean always-up baseline: {results_df['always_up_baseline'].mean():.1%}\")\n","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-13T19:23:58.080572Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-13T19:23:58.081025Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-13T19:23:58.981716Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-13T19:23:58.080964Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-13T19:23:58.980247Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"   fold  test_start    test_end  model_accuracy  always_up_baseline  \\\n0     1  2024-02-05  2024-07-29        0.496129            0.486907   \n1     2  2024-07-31  2025-01-23        0.513876            0.491779   \n2     3  2025-01-27  2025-07-21        0.496738            0.506655   \n3     4  2025-07-23  2026-01-13        0.502914            0.480470   \n4     5  2026-01-15  2026-07-10        0.517007            0.483515   \n\n   n_test_rows  \n0        11495  \n1        11495  \n2        11495  \n3        11495  \n4        11495  \n\nMean model accuracy: 50.5%\nMean always-up baseline: 49.0%\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":7},{"id":"c38aca12-0c6a-4b96-bd57-5f4d42d2d548","cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Result:** ~50%, consistently, across every fold. This held true across\ndaily/weekly/monthly/3-month horizons, across a simple linear model\n(Logistic Regression) as well as a more flexible one (Gradient Boosting),\nand confidence-bucket analysis showed the model's *most* confident\npredictions were **not** more accurate than its least confident ones —\ni.e. its confidence scores carried no real calibration.\n\nThat's a genuine, well-tested null result for price/volume-only technical\nfeatures on large-cap daily-to-quarterly horizons. Consistent with the\nbroader, well-known reality that liquid markets are hard to beat with\npublic technical signals alone.","metadata":{}},{"id":"0259a8f4-92eb-4d19-836e-110e15798bbf","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 4. Sentiment as a Last, Pre-Registered Test\n\nBefore running this test, we set a bar: **sentiment only gets built into\nthe live product's confidence model if it clears 55% accuracy.** Set in\nadvance, specifically so the result couldn't be rationalized after seeing it.\n\n**Data:** AAII Investor Sentiment Survey — weekly, publicly documented\nsince 1987, a well-known contrarian indicator (extreme bearishness has\nhistorically preceded above-average returns, and vice versa). Official\nAAII export, ~2,000 real weekly readings, current through mid-2026.\n\n**Setup:** monthly resolution (to match sentiment's natural cadence),\npooled across ~47 tickers, 5-fold walk-forward validation, same\nmarket-adjusted excess-return target as above.","metadata":{}},{"id":"e5a79093-0e56-4f61-9810-4b90bc8529b5","cell_type":"markdown","source":"```\n                accuracy_without_sentiment   accuracy_with_sentiment\nMean                              48.8%                       50.7%\nAlways-up baseline:                                           51.2%\n\n>>> 55% threshold: NOT MET <<<\n```\n\n**Verdict:** sentiment gave a small, real lift over price/volume alone\n(48.8% → 50.7%) — but didn't clear the pre-set bar, and neither version\nbeat the \"always predict up\" baseline for this period. Per our own rule,\n**sentiment stays as a displayed data point on the live dashboard, not as\nan input to the confidence score.**","metadata":{}},{"id":"9bddc43d-b867-454b-a992-4f3d42514cd9","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 5. What This Means for the Live Product\n\n- Confidence scores shown on [lay4cast.com](https://lay4cast.com) are\n  deliberately capped to a realistic 45–65% band — not because the model\n  is broken, but *because* this testing showed raw model confidence isn't\n  calibrated, and displaying an inflated number (e.g. \"95% confidence\")\n  would be actively misleading.\n- The 3 core layers (hourly volume, weekly trend, seasonal pattern) and the\n  4th layer (AAII + analyst sentiment) are shown as **transparent inputs**,\n  not as a black-box guarantee.\n- This is a free, beta tool built by one person, using real data and real\n  validation, with the honest result stated plainly: **it does not reliably\n  beat the market.** Treat it as one input among many, not a signal to\n  trade on alone.\n\n**Feedback, corrections, and forks are genuinely welcome** — if you find a\nbug in this methodology (including in the leakage fix, the validation\nfolds, or the sentiment test), please say so. That's the whole point of\npublishing it this way.","metadata":{}}]}